# rcm config — controls how `rcup` from ~/.dotfiles is applied to $HOME.
#
# DIRS lists directories inside ~/.dotfiles that rcm should RECURSE INTO,
# symlinking each contained file individually instead of symlinking the
# whole directory as one unit.
#
# Why this matters for `claude/`:
#   ~/.claude/ holds Claude Code's runtime state (sessions/, projects/,
#   todos/, history.jsonl, credentials, plugin caches, etc.) that must
#   stay machine-local and writable. If rcm symlinked the whole ~/.claude
#   directory to ~/.dotfiles/claude, it would clobber that runtime state.
#
# By recursing, only the specific files we drop into ~/.dotfiles/claude/
# (CLAUDE.md, agents/*.md, skills/*, commands/*, keybindings.json, ...)
# get symlinked into ~/.claude/, and everything else Claude writes there
# is left untouched.
#
# Add more entries here if other tools have the same "shared config files
# living next to local runtime state" pattern.
DIRS="claude"
